==Strategy==
Ice warriors have good accuracy and can cut through [[Ranged]] and [[Magic]] armour with ease. They also seem to have higher levels of aggression than many other mobs as they'll often engage the player from a rather long distance. Food such as [[Swordfish]] or better is advised. Wearing [[Adamant armour|adamant]] or [[Rune armour]] will be a good option, as the warrior's melee attacks will be less effective. Ice warriors are weak against magic spells and crush weapons.

In the [[Asgarnian Ice Dungeon]], they can be [[safespot]]ted by trapping an ice warrior on one side of a plus shaped formation of rocks (not to be confused with the floor ice spikes) in the north-western area of their room.

At the [[White Wolf Mountain]] they can be safespotted directly south of the dungeon marker, or in the ladder area (1 step west of middle ladder or east of tree. Switch to another warrior if they pull you from your spot). This method requires a [[pickaxe]] and level 50 [[Mining]] to clear the landslide.

